gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Celtics 144, Kings 119
gameRecap.excerpt: The Celtics defeated the Kings, 144-119. Jaylen Brown led the way for the Celtics with 28 points, five rebounds and six assists, while Derrick White (28 points, seven assists, six 3PM) and Jrue Holiday (season-high 21 points, eight rebounds, 10 assists) added a combined 49 points in the victory. DeAaron Fox tallied 29 points and six 3PM for the Kings in the losing effort. The Celtics improve to 21-6 on the season, while the Kings fall to 16-10.
